        • emailRegex
          String emailRegex
          Represents the regular expression pattern to validate email addresses. The email address must have the format local_part@domain. It must contain at least one character before the "@" symbol, followed by the "@" symbol, and then the domain name with at least one dot.
        • emailRegexPattern
          Pattern emailRegexPattern
          The compiled pattern for validating email addresses.
        • passwordRegex
          String passwordRegex
          Represents the regular expression pattern to validate passwords. Passwords must be between 8 and 16 characters long and contain at least one uppercase letter, one lowercase letter, one number, and one special character.
        • passwordRegexPattern
          Pattern passwordRegexPattern
          The compiled pattern for validating passwords.
        • usernameRegex
          String usernameRegex
          Represents the regular expression pattern to validate usernames. Usernames must be between 3 and 20 characters long and consist of alphanumeric characters. They cannot start or end with a special character (_,-, or .) and cannot have consecutive special characters.
        • usernameRegexPattern
          Pattern usernameRegexPattern
          The compiled pattern for validating usernames.
